%[text] # LLC Converter Power Circuit Library Block
%[text] This block models the power circuit of an LLC resonant converter. It uses the full bridge converter in the primary and full bridge diode bridge rectifier in the transformer secondary. The transformer leakage inductance is used as a series resonant inductor. You can choose between different switch and diode models to suit your application and simulation requirements.
%[text] - **Primary Semiconductor Switch**: Select between Ideal Semiconductor Switch, MOSFET without thermal port, and Tabulated MOSFET with thermal port.
%[text] - **Secondary Diode**: Select between Ideal Diode and Tabulated Diode. \
%[text] The block consists of three main subsystems:
%[text] - Inverter (Primary Side)
%[text] - Resonant Tank
%[text] - Rectifier (Secondary Side) \
%[text] This flexible structure allows for efficient simulation of various LLC converter topology and device characteristics.
%[text] ## Mask Icon
%[text] ![](text:image:7923)
%[text] ## Ports
%[text:table]
%[text] | Port | Description |
%[text] | --- | --- |
%[text] | G | Primary ground |
%[text] | P1 | Primary positive input |
%[text] | N1 | Primary negative input |
%[text] | P2 | Secondary positive output |
%[text] | N2 | Secondary negative output |
%[text] | Meas | Measurement output |
%[text:table]
%[text] ## Parameters
%[text] **Resonant Tank Parameters**
%[text:table]
%[text] | Parameter | Variable Name | Description |
%[text] | --- | --- | --- |
%[text] | Resonant capacitance (F) | Cr | Capacitance of the resonant tank |
%[text] | Primary leakage inductance (H) | Lk1 | Primary side leakage inductance |
%[text] | Primary resistance (Ohm) | R1 | Resistance in the primary winding |
%[text] | Secondary leakage inductance (H) | Lk2 | Secondary side leakage inductance |
%[text] | Secondary resistance (Ohm) | R2 | Resistance in the secondary winding |
%[text] | Magnetizing inductance (H) | Lm | Magnetizing inductance |
%[text] | Transformer primary turns (N1) | N1 | Number of primary turns |
%[text] | Transformer secondary turns (N2) | N2 | Number of secondary turns |
%[text] | Output filter capacitance (F) | Co | Output filter capacitance |
%[text] | Output filter ESR (Ohm) | Rco | Output filter equivalent series resistance |
%[text:table]
%[text] **Primary Semiconductor Switch**
%[text:table]
%[text] | Parameter | Variable Name | Description |
%[text] | --- | --- | --- |
%[text] | Select primary switching device | primaryDeviceOption | Choose the switch model  (Ideal Switch/Ideal MOSFET without Thermal/Ideal MOSFET with Thermal) |
%[text] | On-state resistance (Ohm) | Ron | MOSFET on-state resistance |
%[text] | Off-state conductance (1/Ohm) | Goff | MOSFET off-state conductance |
%[text] | Threshold voltage (V) | Vth | MOSFET threshold voltage |
%[text] | Body diode forward voltage (V) | VbodydiodeOn | MOSFET body diode forward voltage |
%[text] | Body diode on-resistance (Ohm) | RbodydiodeOn | MOSFET body diode on-resistance |
%[text] | Body diode off-conductance (1/Ohm) | GbodydiodeOff | MOSFET body diode off-conductance |
%[text] | MOSFET parasitic capacitance (F) | Cparasitic | MOSFET output capacitance |
%[text:table]
%[text] **Secondary Diode**
%[text:table]
%[text] | Parameter | Variable Name | Description |
%[text] | --- | --- | --- |
%[text] | Select secondary diode | secondaryDeviceOption | Choose the diode model (Ideal Diode/Tabulated Diode) |
%[text] | Forward voltage (V) | VsdiodeOn | Diode forward voltage |
%[text] | On resistance (Ohm) | RsdiodeOn | Diode on-state resistance |
%[text] | Off conductance (1/Ohm) | GsdiodeOff | Diode off-state conductance |
%[text:table]
%[text] ## LLC Resonant Converter Power Circuit Internal Structure
%[text] LLC resonant converter power circuit has three subsystem, those are:
%[text] - **Inverter**: Full-bridge with three MOSFET fidelity.
%[text] - **Resonant Tank**: Contains Cr, Lk1, Lk2, Lm, R1, R2, N1, N2.
%[text] - **Rectifier**: Full-bridge with two diode fidelity. \
%[text] ![](text:image:4a79)
%[text] ### Primary Inverter
%[text]  The primary inverter is made-up of a full bridge single phase inverter with four semiconductor switches. 
%[text] ![](text:image:6f7a)
%[text] You can choose between three inverter fidelities modeled using variant subsystem.
%[text] - Ideal Switch
%[text] - Ideal MOSFET without Thermal
%[text] - Ideal MOSFET with Thermal \
%[text] ![](text:image:2b96)
%[text] ## Resonant Tank
%[text] This LLC resonant converter Power Circuit library block uses the Nonlinear Transformer block from Simscape™ Electrical library to model the resonant tank. The leakage inductance of the transformer is used as a series resonant inductor and the magnetizing inductance is used as a parallel resonant inductor. ![](text:image:04da)
%[text] ## Rectifier Subsystem
%[text] This LLC resonant converter Power Circuit library block uses full bridge diode bridge rectifier. 
%[text] ![](text:image:93ab)
%[text] You can choose between two rectifier fidelity modeled using variant subsystem.
%[text] - Ideal Diode
%[text] - Tabulated Diode \
%[text] ![](text:image:0baa)
